30/06/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- On the sidelines of the NATO summit Tuesday (29 June), the foreign ministers of Croatia, Albania and Macedonia met and agreed to boost military co-operation. Miomir Zuzul, Kastriot Islami and Ilinka Mitreva signed a joint declaration that pledged to "continue with intensive co-operation of our three countries in all important fields, helping each other on the road towards NATO". (HINA - 30/06/04)
